story: Abdelrhman Ibrahim shared AB3D's photo to the group: Egyptian Geeks.
name: AB3D
description:
3D printing
HOW IT WORKS:
3D printers replace ink with everything from plastic to chocolate to concrete,and instead of spiting out a flat ink on paper product,they stack thousands upon thousands of extremely thin printed layers on top of each other to create complex three-dimensional objects
 
THEN AND NOW:
In 1996 the Z402 printer costed:50,000$ weighed 300 pounds and it's speed was 0.014 mm/second
In 2014 the DA VINCI 1.0 costed:499$    weighed 52  pounds and it's speed was 150 mm/second

3D Printers shipped worldwide: 
In 2013 it was 79,000 ,in 2014 was 133,000 and in 2015 217,350 was shipped
The 3D printed Market size would be 21 billion dollars 

Many 3D Printing Markets are Massive:
Medical :$46 Million
Architecture:$88 Million
Consumer:$89 Million
Automotive:$118 Million
Aerospace:$142 Million

Today we can Print:
Fancy chocolate,Titanium jaws,Apartment buildings,Fighter jet parts and much much more
